# Security Policy for PDFusion

## Security Practices

### Electron Security
- ✅ Context isolation enabled
- ✅ Node integration disabled
- ✅ Web security enabled
- ✅ Secure preload script with controlled API exposure
- ✅ No dangerous permissions exposed to renderer

### Dependencies
- ✅ Regular security audits via `npm audit`
- ✅ Automatic dependency updates for security patches
- ✅ Minimal dependency footprint

### File Handling
- ✅ File operations sandboxed through Electron's secure APIs
- ✅ No direct file system access from renderer
- ✅ Temporary files properly cleaned up
- ✅ Input validation for file paths

### Code Security
- ✅ No hardcoded secrets or credentials
- ✅ Environment variables properly handled
- ✅ CORS headers configured
- ✅ TypeScript for type safety

### Build Security
- ✅ Development files excluded from production builds
- ✅ Source maps disabled in production
- ✅ Secure build process without external scripts

## Security Checklist

Before each release:
- [ ] Run `npm audit` and fix any vulnerabilities
- [ ] Review all file operations and API exposures
- [ ] Ensure no sensitive data in repository
- [ ] Verify .gitignore covers all sensitive patterns
- [ ] Test in production build environment
- [ ] Verify Electron security best practices

## Reporting Security Issues

Please report security vulnerabilities to: security@[your-domain]
